INSERT INTO player_duties VALUES(1,'2025-26',1,'GK','Initiate the short build-up (distribute to full-backs/CBs even under pressure — a fixed principle), command the box, cover the full penalty-area width behind a mid-block; sweeping is situational, not constant.','Measured (3 matches): centroid pinned to his own goal-line (x~10.1-10.5), laterally central (y~46-53); broad shallow coverage across the full box width; one match shows the furthest off-line range — sweeping only when the game demanded. High action volume (74+ in one match).','HIGH — deep base + full-width coverage + build-up involvement exactly match the brief; no evidence of over-aggressive sweeping that would break the mid-block.','gk_sweeper/Build-Up is right for the build-up brief; measured depth says the sweeping is situational, so Balanced focus is acceptable in match variants (used in the 로저스 CAM preset).','appearances player_id=1 ranks 1-3 (measured); tactic_observations build_up','MEDIUM-HIGH — heatmaps HIGH (API-measured); note top-3 selection bias (best matches only).');
INSERT INTO player_duties VALUES(2,'2025-26',2,'RB','Defend-first right-back: contain the opposing winger, hold the right touchline width, advance only one-at-a-time with the left FB (foundation rule), late box arrivals when Villa dominate.','Measured (3 matches): y~15-20 in every match — never drifts inside. Flank HEIGHT varies with the brief: one match defensive-leaning (def 38%/mid 42%), one balanced (def 29%/mid 41%), one camped high (mid 46%/att 32%).','HIGH — width discipline is absolute; height modulates per game plan exactly as the one-at-a-time rule predicts.','fb_fullback/Versatile (optimal) fits the height modulation; switch to Defend focus for containment briefs (e.g. vs Liverpool, 로저스 CAM preset).','appearances player_id=2 ranks 1-3 (measured); tactic_observations in_possession/modulation','MEDIUM-HIGH — heatmaps HIGH; top-3 bias noted.');
INSERT INTO player_duties VALUES(3,'2025-26',3,'RCB','Right-side duel/aerial anchor, cover behind the advancing Cash, step out with the ball into right-centre midfield in possession, far-post set-piece threat.','Measured (3 matches): def|right 35-50% core, mid|centre 20-34% step-ins (largest vs Forest, x-centroid 33.6 in the highest-line match), att-third spikes only on set pieces (header goal vs Bologna away).','HIGH — textbook match between brief and footprint; the step-out carries are measured, not just narrated.','cb_defender/Balanced confirmed — measured midfield step-ins argue for Balanced over a pure-stopper Defend focus.','appearances 72-74 (measured); tactic_observations defence','MEDIUM-HIGH — heatmaps HIGH; top-3 bias noted.');
INSERT INTO player_duties VALUES(4,'2025-26',4,'LCB','Left ball-playing CB: progress via carries and passes into the left half-space, feed Digne/Maatsen and the inverted left attack, step into midfield when Villa pin teams back; box arrivals on set pieces.','Measured (3 matches): y~67-71 left-centre constant. Depth scales with control: deep vs Bologna (70% own third), stepping into the middle third vs Fulham (54% mid) and Forest (x up to 97 — header + penalty won). Attacking-third volume near zero in open play.','HIGH — progression happens by stepping UP the left-centre channel, exactly the BPD brief; never wanders off the left channel.','cb_bpd/Build-Up confirmed unambiguously.','appearances player_id=4 ranks 1-3 (measured); tactic_observations build_up','MEDIUM-HIGH — heatmaps HIGH; top-3 bias noted.');
INSERT INTO player_duties VALUES(5,'2025-26',5,'LB','Two-way left-back: hold the left touchline width for the inverted attack (Rogers cuts in, Digne provides width), advance one-at-a-time opposite Cash, deliver crosses/cutbacks; balance defensive recovery with attacking output.','Measured (3 matches): y~82-84 touchline-hugging in all three; average height climbs 45→51→53 with attacking-third share 21%→35%→41% depending on the brief; 52-86 touches, big two-way volume.','HIGH — constant width, modulated height; the cutback assist vs Liverpool (Rogers goal) is the duty executed at its peak.','fb_fullback/Versatile (optimal) fits; fb_wingback/Support for attacking variants — both already present in the DB/tool presets.','appearances player_id=5 ranks 1-3 (measured); tactic_observations in_possession','MEDIUM-HIGH — heatmaps HIGH; top-3 bias noted.');
INSERT INTO player_duties VALUES(6,'2025-26',6,'LB','Attacking left-back variant (vs Digne''s balanced profile): high-and-wide starting position, runs through the left half-space to the byline, create overloads with the inverted left winger; still owns the full left-channel defensive lane.','Measured (3 matches): avg height 44-56/100 (well past a normal FB), y~81-83; end-to-end left channel coverage in every match — own box to opposition byline; goal vs Maccabi from a byline run; Brentford match: 115 heat points, 100 touches, 6 tackles.','HIGH — the most front-foot footprint of any defender measured, and the two-way volume shows the defensive lane isn''t abandoned.','fb_att_wb/Attack (bench mapping) confirmed; select him over Digne when the plan needs left-side overloads rather than crossing balance.','appearances player_id=6 ranks 1-3 (measured); tactic_observations modulation axis 4','MEDIUM-HIGH — heatmaps HIGH; top-3 bias noted.');
INSERT INTO player_duties VALUES(7,'2025-26',12,'LDM','Pivot anchor: screen the back four, sit left-of-centre (balancing McGinn''s right side), controlled circulation, cover for the advancing left side; occasional forward carries.','Measured (3 matches): left-of-centre discipline is constant (y~36-37, 48-52% left-side share). BUT depth contradicts the "deep screen" label: defensive-third share only 13-38%, middle third 47-66%, and vs Wolves/Forest he averaged PAST halfway (x~52-54) with 18-30% attacking-third volume, reaching both boxes.','HIGH on lane discipline; PARTIAL on the "deep anchor" framing — in dominant wins he operates as a controlling pivot around halfway, not a sitting destroyer. (Bias caveat: top-3 matches are dominant wins, where the pivot naturally plays higher.)','dm_holding/Ball-Winning may undersell him — measured footprint in controlled games looks closer to dm_dlp or a Roaming holding profile. Flag: review player_role_map before finalising; collect 1-2 heatmaps from tighter/away matches to de-bias first.','appearances player_id=12 ranks 1-3 (measured); tactic_observations modulation','MEDIUM — heatmaps HIGH but the top-3 dominance bias directly affects the conclusion; needs a difficult-match sample.');
INSERT INTO player_duties VALUES(8,'2025-26',16,'ST','Lone striker, three briefs in one: (1) occupy the central box for wide deliveries, (2) drop/link and lay off to the inside-cutting Rogers/McGinn, (3) run the channels in behind as the transition outlet (drift wide to open the box for the 10).','Measured (3 matches): all three briefs visible and cleanly separated by game type — Sunderland: near-pure central box occupation (2 headers from wide deliveries); Liverpool: central box + left-channel link play with Rogers; Man City (away, counter brief): deeper average, transition lanes halfway-to-box, central-right channel bursts.','HIGH — the footprint reshapes per game plan while the goal output stays constant (2 goals in each of the three matches); this is the system''s most brief-obedient attacker.','st_advanced/Versatile confirmed exactly — Versatile captures the box-occupier/link/channel-runner trinity better than Attack (pure poacher) would.','appearances player_id=16 ranks 1-3 (measured); tactic_observations in_possession','MEDIUM-HIGH — heatmaps HIGH; top-3 bias noted but the three matches happen to span three distinct game types (home rout, home clash, away counter), which mitigates it.');
